  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one evening I recall that we went through a portion of a suburb of the city of Budapest, where one city-- one-- a street of the city was dug out for trank-- tank entrapment.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the sidewalk was taken away, and the traffic of the street was taken away and dug out for a big continuous wall of the entire neighborhood, for tank entrapment, if, if whoever, the occupying forces or the Russians will come, that they slow down the advance with this, that the tanks wouldn't be able to cross it, because it's a ditch.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And pouring rain, and we were walking one that very narrow side of the street which was left.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And constantly, shootings in the air, terror, to move faster.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people were in mud and sliding in the rain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And some people slid down to the ditch and couldn't come up in the mud.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then if somebody was left behind, they just shoot into the crowd who was helping them, to-- it says continue and don't help the people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then it was fear and, and, and awful scene that we were just like herds of animal led to to our next location.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that entailed no more work, after that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But we were taken to places like the brick factory, [HUNGARIAN] in Hungarian, which was very well known to all of us who went through that location.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in that brick factory, some on the courtyard of it, some in the factory itself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And some of the brick, brick-- if you ever seen a brick, a brick factory, which I didn't see until that moment, some of these where they dried the bricks were little cups, where heat came in.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
